SIMPLE: gloat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gloat
<hw>Gloat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Gloated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gloating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to Icel. <ets>glotta</ets>
to smile scornfully, G. <ets>glotzen</ets> to gloat.]</ety> <def>To look
steadfastly; to gaze earnestly; to gaze with passionate desire, lust, or
avarice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To gaze with malignant satisfaction; to exult
maliciously, sometimes also triumphantly, in another's loss or
discomfort; -- usually in a bad sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In vengeance <qex>gloating</qex> on another's pain.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>glob</ent>⟦br⟧
